    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://chicago.craigslist.org/nch/lab/6041852194.html"></div>
        </div>
We are a north suburban processing plant seeking motivated machine operators for immediate hire! Please apply in person only!<br>
<br>
Summary: Perform production on equipment including machine operation activities that do not involve control other than start, stop or inspect. Typically this involves feeding, sorting, or packaging the product. Responsible for machine operation and cleanliness of equipment that will apply material or self locking devices for fasteners by performing the following duties: <br>
<br>
1. Responsible for understanding machine operation.*<br>
2. Monitors production rates.*<br>
3. Inspection. Conduct inspections and/or tests to verify product conformance. Depending on<br>
assignment, may work with set-ups (first piece inspection), parts in-process (line inspection),<br>
finished product (final inspection), subcontracted parts, or tooling*<br>
4. Problem Resolution. Report nonconformance and, with assistance, determine dispositions and<br>
process deviations. Provide input into the resolution of problems.*<br>
5. General assistance. Provide assistance in containment procedures, monitoring of new or difficult<br>
parts and removal of all set-up &amp; processing scrap between jobs.*<br>
6. Documentation. Initiate, complete or verify records documenting quality management system<br>
activities to assure compliance to internal procedures, customer requirements and ISO<br>
17025/ISO 9001:2000 standards; where applicable*<br>
7. Adheres to safety guidelines.*<br>
8. Adheres to 5S methods and practices.*<br>
9. Follow all procedures, work instructions and forms*<br>
10. All other duties as assigned by the supervisor or designated person<br>
Qualifications:<br>
To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily.<br>
The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required.<br>
Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<br>
<br>
Language Ability:<br>
Ability to read a limited number of two and three syllable words and to recognize similarities and<br>
differences between words and between series numbers, preferred. Ability to print and speak simple<br>
sentences, preferred.<br>
<br>
Math Ability:<br>
A minimum ability to add and subtract two digit numbers.<br>
<br>
Reasoning Ability:<br>
Ability to apply common sense understanding to carry out detailed but uninvolved written or oral<br>
instructions.<br>
<br>
Education/Experience:<br>
High school diploma or general education degree (GED) preferred; and less than one year related<br>
experience or training; or equivalent combination of education and experience, preferred.<br>
Specialized Training:<br>
Feeder bowl operation adjustment experience (Optional)<br>
<br>
Equipment, potential to use:<br>
• Fork lift (optional and with training)<br>
• Measurement Gages<br>
• Stop Watch<br>
• Zahn Cup<br>
<br>
Knowledge, Skills, and Other Abilities:<br>
• Ability to adjust to changing work assignments and conditions<br>
• Knowledge of and experience with electromechanical machine adjustments, motor speeds, feed<br>
rates, and identification of machine problems resulting in down time<br>
• Minimal computer skills (optional)<br>
<br>
Physical Demands:<br>
The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to<br>
successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to<br>
enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<br>
While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to stand, walk, use hands,<br>
reach with hands and arms, and talk and hear. The employee is occasionally required to sit, climb or<br>
balance, stoop, kneel, crouch or crawl, and smell. The employee must frequently lift and/or move up to 50 pounds. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, distance vision, peripheral vision, depth perception, ability to adjust focus, and ability to see color. The employee must be able to wear personal protective equipment including, but not limited to, safety glasses meeting ANSI Z87 requirements and hearing protection devices.<br>
<br>
Work Environment:<br>
The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee<br>
encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be<br>
made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<br>
<br>
Compensation: $13.50/hr<br>
Union Position<br>
Benefits: Health, Life, Dental, 401K<br>
<br>
Apply in person only! <br>
ND Industries <br>
1840 Raymond Drive<br>
Northbrook, IL 60062<br>
    </section>

